{
  "stem": "1033.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and even though I had told you a dreadful tale which happened to me, there were heartening aspects of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like the guard giving me-- I am me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I only know me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I may be looking at you and looking even at my kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But really, I have a glancing acquaintance with myself and less with others, even though observation does help for us to kind of position ourselves in terms of the rest of humankind.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I find that, that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the war, in many ways, apart from being a personal pain, is a giant embarrassment to me.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I feel really embarrassed for the Germans-- for people, for people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I always looked at the guards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I even looked at Mengele as an extension of myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and there are a couple of things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's really a fantasy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I will tell you, for whatever it's worth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My, my grandfather's mother was the daughter of the very famous Rabbi Jungreis.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's a well-known, very religious, even today, Orthodox Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there are some rabbis today by the name of Jungreis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I just wondered if somehow, maybe his godliness and his goodness, through his genes, I had inherited something that will survive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And what-- how that connects to the concept of God, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I wouldn't spend too much time trying to identify it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What-- the other thing is that, that taking that as, as part of me, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when I look out through my eyes, I see people.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I assume that they're very much like myself.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
